reviews: We had a great stay. The hotel feels like a boutique hotel. The swimmingpool was great for my daughter. The room was spacious. Breakfast great. Nice restaurants in the neighborhood (Bong). The only suggestion I could make is to do something about the chairs in the breakfastroom. The sliding of the chairs on the tile floor can be heard at the 3th Floor (but I am very soundsensitive)

The neighbourhood if the hotel is nice with different shops an restaurants/bars. The beds are comfortables and the rooms nice. We shared a room as a family of 3 for two nights. For a longer stay we would prefer a larger room. We enjoyed the spa in the basement of the hotel.

I came here as an anniversary gift for my wife and I The rooms are extremely small, the staff wasn’t friendly or responsive. No bell boy to help with luggage. Food was awful
Not accommodating. Wouldn’t recommend anyone to stay here

Amazing staff - lovely rooms - phenomenal location where you feel that you actually live in the 15th arrondisement with close access to tourist sites.

I wish we had a longer stay - but, I look forward to our next trip as this is our go-to hotel moving forward.

Thank you for the lovely staff for taking wonderful care of us.

It was a great experience to stay here. Great helpful staff and clean and good rooms. Sauna and Pool facilities are maintained really well. It is reasonably close to Eiffel Tower. Breakfast spread was reasonable as well.

The hotel is in a nice and quiet area from Paris. Within 20 minutes you are in the centre.
The rooms are very comfortable and spacious.The bathroom was a highlight.
The breakfast was very good but the waiters were a bit disordered. The bar and the reception team are great.

Overall very good experience; room was very confortable with a decent size; bathroom was very ample and amenities were excellent; staff at reception very agreeable and knowledgeable; breakfast buffet was extremely rich with a very wide selection of various types of BF options;
the only bothering thing was that the cleaning staff were using the main guests elevators which was somewhat bothersome in terms of waiting time to get inside an elevator. A part form this my experience was very good.

We had a great time at Hotel Eiffel Blomet! The location was perfect - a lovely neighbourhood in the 15th Arr, surrounded by patisseries, boulangeries, and other nice spots to eat and drink.

It was also very well connected to the main areas you’ll likely keen be to go when holidaying in Paris - 30 mins from most spots on the Metro and just over 20 minutes away from the Eiffel Tower and Montparnasse on foot!

The balcony in our room was a great surprise feature, with spectacular views of the Eiffel Tower’s victory lap at night, as were the spa facilities, which we enjoyed daily.

Thank you Hotel Eiffel Blomet for having us!

A stay at the Hotel Eiffel Blomet is a home away from home. This hotel is perfectly located. You get to experience Parisian life in a residential area that has everything at your disposal and you are close enough to other arrondisments and landmarks. I would recommed this Hotel for anyone. I will definitely return to Hotel Eiffel Blomet.

I enjoied very much my stay at Hotel Eiffel Blomet. It´s very well located near underground. Nearby you have many different restaurants. The hotel itself is very quiet with confortable beds and good bathrooms. The breakfast is good. The swimming pool and fitness room are very good options after a day in the city. Very helpful and english speaking staff. Thank you very much!

Travelled in a group of 10 with family and friends including 4 teenagers. My oldest daughter and another teenager on the trip had stayed in October and recommended that we stay here, so glad they did. It’s a lovely stylish hotel with brilliant staff, so friendly and helpful. Rooms are clean as was the pool area and communal areas. We had the breakfast a couple of times which was great. We all also really loved the location. The Metro is a few minutes away with very easy access to the centre of Paris. It’s a really nice area; residential as well as some tourists, lovely independent shops and some restaurants. We particularly enjoyed Wallace and Blomet. We all said we would stay here again as it has such a lovely feel.

Gem of a hotel. Lovely location for exploring Paris. Hotel very welcoming with pleasant sitting area. Great pool, steam room and gym. Amazing breakfast. Staff very helpful. Rooms were small but we had everything we needed.

A very nicely located and kept hotel in a cosy, not too touristy area. Nice pool, sauna, hammam, good breakfast. When we were there, sauna wasn't operating and the hammam was cold, but I'm sure that was just bad luck. The breakfast is good and worth the price. Could maybe need a few touches to make it perfect. I'd definitely come back!

We had a wonderful stay at the Hotel Eiffel Blomet. The staff were wonderful. The pool and amenities were as advertised and very enjoyable. The morning breakfast was a good price for the quality of food and our under 10 aged child ate for free. Would enthusiastically recommend to anyone going to Paris.

Hotel Eiffel Blomet - offers great breakfast, nice pool w/ sauna, steam room and gym. The hotel is surrounded by various specialty restaurants and markets. 30min walk to the Le Bon Marche’ (designers shopping mall) and Eiffel Tower. Rooms are compact, they used the space well with all ingenious cabinets and storage spaces- coffee, tea and condiments provided. The bathrooms are modern design with good shower pressure. All staff - front desk - Roxane, Benjamin thank you for making sure we have access to pool/spa while waiting, housekeeper, security and especially the breakfast crew Sunny, Emilie and Clarisse are incredibly gracious, friendly and accommodating. “Nous sommes très reconnaissants”. We are very grateful.

We were very impressed with this hotel. The rooms and location was perfect.
Clean bed linen and towels every day! Room had all you needed, nice bathroom, tea/coffee facilities, air con and heating, very comfortable bed, safe, tv and hair dryer, wifi and all working and in very good condition. Breakfast was great and optional which is super
Staff were great and having the pool and spa was an additional treat.

The Honesty Bar is advertised incorrectly on the website. They don't have a bar but an option to have wine or beer. You need the hotel staff to tab a card before you help yourself to a drink which is then added to your bill for payment on departure. This service closes at 10pm. So no alcohol after 10pm in the hotel They do have a mini bar in the room but only beer, water and soft drinks in this.

Great stay in March and great location to get around sightseeing in Paris. Loved the spa and pool facilities to relax in after busy days. great access to bus and metro and excellent local brassieres close by including the Wallace, small bistro at the end of the road when you leave the hotel on the right side and blomet a little further on.

We stayed as a family of 3 in February, really enjoyed the pool, the cleanliness and the breakfast. They provided great recommendations for the restaurants nearby, we really enjoyed the refined cuisine at L’Inattendu. It is not very close to Eiffel Tower but we are people who like walking so for us there was no issue, there is a metro station close to the hotel for people who prefer using the transport. The only small improvement to be done is to provide more toiletries, specifically cotton swabs and cotton pads because they were not enough for 3 people. At the same time we didn’t ask for additional and I am sure they would have gladly provided.

The hotel is located near a spacious parking garage as well as closet to the main metro 12 line leading to all the important monuments and department stores/shopping areas downtown. The rooms are cozy and well maintained. Having a good bed with clean and good quality sheets. Nice and comfortable bathroom. Rooms have a cooker and a coffee machine. The hotel breaths quality in everything, The bar could however be converted to a real bar where you can enjoy a drink when returning from i.e. a day at work. Or a day of sightseeing.

Had a brilliant stay here.
The room was very clean.
Has amazing toiletries.
The Chrome cast in the room is fantastic.
The swimming pool and spa is incredible.
It was the perfect hotel for our Christmas in Paris.

The hotel was a lovely boutique in Paris. It was small and clean and the staff were very friendly. The room was a little on the small side and didn’t have much of a view but it was clean, the bed was comfy and there were some innovative storage solutions. There wasn’t much in the local area but you’re not too far from public transport to get into the main city.

The hotel it’s in an excellent location,car park accessible 24 / 24 h not far ,excellent and friendly staff .
Nice and clean room , great spa and swimming pool area available all day.
Not too far from the centre

My family and I stayed at this hotel for a birthday weekend away and it didn’t disappoint.

The hotel is clean and staff friendly. Easy to find and close to the metro.

The room was adequately sized for a four night stay and plenty of room for two Adults and a child. The room was always cleaned and made up when we returned from a day’s sightseeing.

Breakfast was fresh and plenty of choice every day.

The best thing about this hotel (according to my son) was the pool. We used these facilities every day. Only one time did we find it busy but it was a Saturday evening and to be expected.

I’d have no hesitation staying here again and can wholly recommend it to anyone.

Lovely hotel. Good location, close to the metro, and nice things around it. Great service, delicious breakfast, nice facilities. I will definitely stay there again when I come back to Paris. I definitely recommend it.

The best! We came for our honeymoon. It has been stressful because our planned Paris wedding was supposed to be the 17th of Dec., but due to family medical emergency we had to postpone and immediately go to our home country to solemnize our wedding earlier 10th of Dec., so that my father-in-law is still present with us to witness our wedding day.
So we scheduled our honeymoon in this hotel on our original wedding date, and the hotel upgraded our stay to a suite when we checked-in! It was very nice and helped us relax after all the stress and problems that we encountered.
Our planned Paris wedding will be moved in March or April, and we will come back here for another honeymoon. :)
It is now became our favorite hotel, with amazing staff, rooms, breakfast, services, amenities with the spa and pool. We will try to save and treat ourselves from time to time and book in this hotel for our maybe regular or quarterly honeymoon while we're trying to build a family. 🥰

Everything about this hotel exceeded our expectations! The front desk clerks were always pleasant and helpful, the breakfast had everything we could want and was always kept clean and fresh, the room was exactly where we had requested and was cleaned daily, the pool in the basement was such a luxury in a city hotel and we used it each day and the location was incredible for us since we love to walk and could walk wherever we wanted to go. My husband and I love to travel to Paris and this will be our go to hotel from now on.

What a gem! I am just home from 8 nights at Eiffel Blomet Hotel and can not wait to return. It truly felt like a home away from home: quaint and clean with all the small comforts of home (wine and comfy couches in lobby, Nespresso and robe warmer in room); friendly and helpful staff (thank you Benjamin and Lisa who were so patient with my room shifting inquires when my daughter joined mid trip); nestled in the middle of thriving Left Bank neighborhood and 5 minute walk to Metro station. Only sorry that I waited until day 6 to try the pool and spa area. As clean and refreshing as the photos suggest. I am a lap swimmer and was able to actually swim laps - water just right. The steam and sauna were immaculate. Breakfast was fresh and delicious. Truly a wonderful experience and I am known (my kids often tease me about changing rooms) to be highly selective in my hotel accommodations. Merci!!!!

Not cheap, but really very good. I stayed in a junior suite, comfortable and spacey. Free access to the spa was extremely appreciated after a tour of the city all day long. Breakfast is somptuous, with really high quality food and beverage. Possibility of massages and fitness but I didn't access these services. Optimal location near metro and Eiffel tower. Nice places in the surroundings to eat, drink and relax.

A very nice boutique hotel with a good-size room (Deluxe twin room) which is bright, contemporary, and has plenty of cupboard/shelves. It is on a quite street and is only 4 minute walk to the nearest metro station. The staff are very friendly and helpful. It also has a spa and a swimming pool but I was too busy to use!

This very clean Hotel is nested in a convenient part of the posh 15th district (filled with top bakeries, restaurants and bars) a 20mns walk away from the Eiffel tower and near a few metro stops. It is well served by a friendly and motivated young staff who really love their job.
Our room, #204 over looking the inner yard, was big by all parisian standard, approx 20 sqm, doted with a very large closet (well enought for 3 people), where we could find a nespresso machine. The room was super clean, and had in addition to a regular king size bed a sofa that was truly a 1.8m bed where our son slept. The toom was totally soundproofed.

Bathroom had a walk in shower and plenty space for storage, making it convenient for long stays. During our stay the pool was disfunctionnal and we couldnt make use of it, however the hotel compensated us commercially for this gap in service.
The rest of the spa is nice, and offers both Hammam and Sauna, and there is a lovely resting area by the pool, quiet a nice perk in the middle of Paris.
We were annoyed by the fact that 1 of their 2 lifts did not work at all during most of our stay, but luckily we were on the 2nd floor so could manage the situation.
A big thanks to the head receptionnist Camille for her professionnal attitude. I can only recommend this venue if you want to enjoy a quaint stay in a typical part of Paris, and live like a local, but inside the cocoon of this gem boutique hotel. If we come back to Paris we will definitely try to come here again.

The Hotel is is nice and the beds are comfortable. The Staff is friendly and eager to help, although they may not be able to lend any major assistance other than what you can do yourself (for example: calling an Uber or handing you a box to sift through left-over adaptors, if asking for one).
The bathrooms in the room are a bit odd, with the toilet being completely separate from the shower area. There is not much closet space, but plenty of floor space to keep your luggage. The rooms are cleaned daily and there is a nice towel warmer in the bathroom.
The breakfast is very good and worth it, especially if you will be on the run.
A few issues with the hotel that I had:
1 - It is far from the airport and from most major sites. You can take the metro around, but even a Metro ride into the heart of the city or airport takes a long time (usually requiring you to take multiple lines). Uber's were hard to get and with the traffic, the Metro was usually faster. You will need to give yourself plenty of time to get where you are going. I recommend booking a car to get to and from the airport (even the metro station is a bit of a walk and with bags this can get cumbersome).
2 - They only have 2 elevators and one was broken. The elevators are also very small. This meant that you may have to wait a while to catch one. So, again, don't be in a rush. There are stairs, but if you are on an upper floor going up it was not convenient to go up by stairs (though, the view from the upper rooms was better).
3 - Not too many amenities. No concierge either.

We had an amazing stay at Hotel Eiffel Blomet; great location, excellent facility and helpful staff. Very well situated, easy transport (both Metro and RER). Great area with some really nice cafes and restaurants around

Excellent location, clean and comfortable rooms, wonderful staff and very accommodating. I wish we had more time to enjoy all the amenities. And a big thank you to Marianne Lohrer,
Manager of the Hotel.
Richard & Yari

I arrived to be told i had to pay in full in advance with a 250 euro deposit. after much chat this was changed and i paid 50 euro deposit the remainder on departure like most hotels.

Well i have checked out, no final bill, no return of 5o euros, called and messaged no update.

Some of the front desk team a bit sharp takes away from a nice facility in a cute location.

They need to understand people just want to enjoy and relax on vacation not feel on edge.

Booked for just one night, our last in Paris. Interested in the spa and a massage. Both were fantastic. The spa is a hammam spa with a pool, sauna and steam room- which we had all to ourselves. My massage was heavenly and easy to book- just email them. A really nice touch was a pre check in survey. I was able to add a bottle of champagne and cheese plate ready for us in our room at check in. I wouldn't have requested that if not for the survey. They happily stored our bags for a bit and got our room ready early. Room itself was small but nicely appointed and fine for one night. Breakfast was included and it was a very nice spread with scrambled eggs, sausage, ham, breads, granola, yogurt etc.. Would recommend.

I had a great experience at Hotel Eiffel Blomet. The breakfast selection is excellent, rooms clean and well-appointed and the location is convenient to all Paris attractions. Will definitely book again.

Was excited to stay at this hotel with all of the great communication ahead of our visit and initially, we were very impressed with how warm and welcoming the staff was. The room was very clean and comfortable, and the breakfast buffet was great! We were, however, disappointed with the lack of communication after we had continuous issues with Wi-Fi and TV connectivity. The Wi-Fi dropped repeatedly and access to the TV was non-existent throughout the entirety of our stay. And while the staff tried to help troubleshoot by coming to the room, they also made no effort to communicate if there were any tech issues after the fact. Certainly not the end of the world since we were touring the city throughout the day, but it would've been nice to have access to the technology that was offered, or at least been told they were working to fix the issue. Instead, it was ignored. When I addressed it one last time during check out, they finally disclosed there was in fact a problem with tech connectivity. I politely asked if there was anything that could be done in terms of the room price but was told the tech offerings were a "perk" and not included in the price. Why wouldn't it be part of the price when it was presented and detailed at check in? Eventually they agreed to comp two beers taken from the fridge; hardly a reasonable compromise. Bottom line, if we had been informed of the issue during our stay, it wouldn't have bothered us much, if at all. Customer service stands out when mistakes or issues are recognized and communicated openly. We enjoyed our time overall but the lack of transparency and accountability on the part of the hotel was frustrating.

The Good things: it was a clean hotel and the staff were friendly. Convenient location near metro.
The not so good: the wi-fi for us did not work. We would get connected for five minutes then it would stop working. We contacted staff three times during our stay and it was never fixed. As travelers who did not have cell phone service, this was a critical issue for us. Also, the room was extremely small with very little storage. The room size was accurately described but we just did not realize how small it actually was. As part of a two week trip we had two large suitcases. Storage space was very minimal, one side of a small closet was all there was. The other closet was full with a mini bar and coffee. This made it awkward for us to be comfortable in the room. If we had just been there for a weekend with a small overnight bag this would not have been an issue. One final thing, there were no wash cloths. We found that a little odd.
Overall I would say this would be fine for a weekend stay but not as a stop on a longer trip and definitely not if you need wifi.

Upon check in, staff was incredibly helpful in providing restaurant recommendations and also called to make reservations for us. Nice room with a comfortable bed. Convenient location being a 15-20 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower. We only stayed 1 night so didn’t have time to try out the Spa, but it sounded lovely. Would definitely return to this hotel with how helpful and welcoming the staff was!

I've stayed here about three times and would gladly come back. The hotel is clean, quiet, and bright, and the personnel are great. My room was small, as is typical for Paris, and the neighborhood was full of delicious food markets, also typical for Paris. The hotel is a bit off the beaten track, but is well connected to the center by subway and bus. A great choice.

This was my second stay at this wonderful hotel. It is calm, clean and relaxed, family friendly and also perfect for adults wanting some quiet time. The rooms are beautiful, cleaned every day, and the breakfast is delicious. The staff were welcoming and super friendly. I would recommend this hotel and can't wait to visit again!

This hotel ticked every box and more. We arrived early after a night in a Sleeper train from Nice. Expecting to be only able to drop off our bags we were offered an early check-in. The staff were very friendly and kind. We had quick showers and went to the indoor swimming pool which has a sauna, tropical storm showers and steam room. What impressed me most was how family friendly the pool was. Normally facilities of this nature would be limited to adults only but like us with our 9-year old there were always other families in the pool with young kids enjoying themselves.

This is a gem of a hotel close to the Eiffel Tower and other sites. Lovely quiet area of Paris with great restaurants, shops. Be a chocolate shop to die for! We will certainly be back.

What a cracking little hotel for a short stay in Paris. Right in the heart of the city and not far from anywhere. We took a deluxe double which included a bed for our child. Not a massive room but big enough and very comfortable with a decent bathroom. Had the best nights sleep here I have had for a long time. Breakfast is wonderful with an incredible spread for a small tourist hotel and the quality was excellent too. The staff were friendly and incredibly helpful in answering any enquiry we had. We stayed here 3 nights and just wished we could have stayed longer.

I recently stayed for 3 nights with my wife and adult daughter. We had a wonderful stay in Paris, made better by this gem of a hotel. The whole hotel is of a very good quality. There are fancier or quirkier hotels, for sure. But this one does the main things extremely well. Reception were very helpful, always quick, friendly and spoke multiple languages. The room was exactly as I expected, nicely finished. Breakfast choice and quality for a buffet was very good. It was 4 mins from Vaugirard metro and about 10 from Commerce, making Paris very accessible. And the pool was a godsend.

We stayed at the Hotel Blomet during our six day holiday in Paris in July. The hotel was clean and comfortable, the staff were helpful and there was a good choice of good quality food for breakfast. The Metro is a 10 minute walk providing quick access to central Paris. Nice swimming pool, sauna and steam room. No hesitation in recommending this hotel.

My family and I had a lovely 4 days in Paris and were delighted with the hotel. Staff super friendly and welcoming. We had a connecting family sweet, one room with two single beds and a bathroom and a larger room with another bathroom and large double bed and good amount of space. The kids and I loved the pool, had a small fitness sweet, steam room, sauna and we had some excellent breakfasts with a great fresh food. Would recommend and we will happily stay again on our next visit.

We had a junior suite 02. Couldn’t fault it. Close to the breakfast room, pool/SPA and reception. The hotel I’d say is a 4 to 5. I’ve given a 5 because the area is vibrant. Full of nice restaurants and you get an immersive feeling given all the locals drinking and eating outside. Very good.

Was not able to make the first night of the booking due to a train delay and was charged full price for the night. Was told that this hotel would be quiet, was put in an inwards facing room that was always loud due to people talking in the plaza inside the hotel. The room was very small for the price albeit clean. Only given two towels and one day when we asked to change the towels room service simply took the two away and didn’t give us any more so we couldn’t take a shower. One of the front desk workers couldn’t speak English even though there was a sign saying they could speak 6 different languages and when we checked out we were almost charged 500 dollars more than what we were supposed to pay for due to an error in their system. Unprofessional to say the least. I don’t know why this place is so expensive nor so overly positively reviewed because at best it’s a three star hotel with terrible management.

Great facilities, convenient location and really helpful friendly staff, highly recommend.

I would say that a variation for breakfasts would make it even better but the quality was consistent

Anytime we wanted to go to a restaurant, the staff would phone & make the reservation for us which was appreciated

Have stayed here for the 3rd time now. Lovely hotel, very nice room, very clean, very good breakfast and everything in walking distance. Next to the hotel is a nice lunch / dinner restaurant and also some small bars for a drink. You can walk in 50 minutes to the Champ Ellysees and near the Eiffel Tower.

If I could give this hotel more stars, I would. This boutique hotel took care with everything. Everyone was helpful and welcoming. The location was perfect - walking distance from cafes, supermarkets, Metro and bus stations....oh and the Eiffel Tower. I suggest you add breakfast to your stay - it was so yummy (and I'm not really a breakfast person). After all the walking we did, it was great to go down to the pool/hammam area for unwinding. I would def stay here again if visiting Paris.

Be careful when booking in this hotel.
We were in the pool area in the basement of the hotel for just 20 minutes, when the room service gained access to our room nicking several items of our personal belongings. Confronted with the situation, the otherwise polite hotel staff got very quiet. As I found out, the hotel is working with an external company which cleans the rooms.

We stayed here for 3 nights and couldn't have enjoyed our stay more! The hotel is very clean and all staff are friendly and approachable. Robes & flip flops provided, stunning bathroom, the shower was amazing and the bed was so comfy! The hotel is situated roughly a 25 minute walk from the Eiffel tower with lots of restaurants & bars on the way. The spa is heaven after a day exploring the sites; decent sized pool & lovely sauna and hammam. We didn't have breakfast however this was available at 17 euros (we preferred to use a local bakery called boulangerie which we found on the way to the Eiffel tower). Overall perfect stay!

My girlfriend and I had a great stay at this hotel. I booked through the Schroders company discount and was provided with a free room upgrade upon arrival. The staff on reception were very friendly and offered us recommendations for our first time in Paris. The room was very nice and modern, with a comfy bed, spacious bathroom and chrome cast built into the TV. I would definitely recommend and we are likely to stay there again if returning to Paris in the future.

Excellent modern Hotel: Friendly and helpful staff, very clean. I enjoyed the sauna and pool. Good amenities such as coffee and tea in the room. I enjoyed my stay a lot! Thank you Eiffel Tower Blomet team!

Clean and modern boutique 4* nested in the convenient posh 15th district (filled with bakeries, restaurants and bars) a 20mns walk from the Eiffel tower and near a few metro stops. It is well served by a friendly and motivated young staff who really love their job.
Our room, #204 over looking the inner yard, was big by all parisian standard, approx 20 sqm, doted with a very large closet (well enought for 3 people), where we could find a nespresso machine. The room was super clean, and had in addition to a regular king size bed a sofa that was truly a 1.8m bed where our son slept. The toom was totally soundproofed.

Bathroom had a walk in shower and plenty space for storage, making it convenient for long stays. During our stay the pool was disfunctionnal and we couldnt make use of it, however the hotel compensated us commercially for this gap in service.
The rest of the spa is nice, and offers both Hammam and Sauna, and there is a lovely resting area by the pool, quiet a nice perk in the middle of Paris.
We were annoyed by the fact that 1 of their 2 lifts did not work at all during most of our stay, but luckily we were on the 2nd floor so could manage the situation.
A big thanks to the head receptionnist Camille for her professionnal attitude. I can only recommend this venue if you want to enjoy a quaint stay in a typical part of Paris, and live like a local, but inside the cocoon of this gem boutique hotel. If we come back to Paris we will definitely try to come here again.

Thank you so much to the staff for an amazing stay, they are so kind and helpful, nothing is too much for them! The rooms are spacious and the bed was so comfortable. Having the spa facilities is a very nice touch too. Amazing location! Will definitely come back again!

We stayed at this hotel in August 2021 - we’ve been to Paris many times however as we were staying slightly longer, we were looking for a hotel with a pool. It is a lovely hotel, super clean, reception staff were fabulous and the pool, sauna and steam room was amazing. You book in each day for a slot and most days found we had the whole spa area to ourselves. Rooms were spacious by Paris standards and had a balcony - we were on 7th floor. Great location, walking distance to Eiffel Tower etc if interested and 5 mins to local metro station. Plenty of bars and restaurants around. We loved it so much we’ve booked to return for a mini moon after our wedding in April. Thank you for a lovely stay!!

charming hotel, good staff, clean, nice spa good area. measures taken for covid that is my 4' th visit to this place. and will come back. good vibes, nice breakfast and staff present at guest request.

we had a most pleasant stay at the Eiffel Blomet. The staff is very helpful and kind, the rooms are clean and spacious and the breakfast is great.
The kids had a great time at the pool. Also great location.
Thanks for a wonderful vacation

I did a reservation via email. Management came back 3 days with 70€ higher price for no reason. I had to cancel the reservation and miss other opportunities with other hotels in the meantime. Absolute shame.

This hotel is convenient to several restaurants, bakeries, cheese shops, etc. About a 10-minute walk to the nearest metro. The staff was friendly, and the facility is clean.

We stayed in room 704 for 8 nights. Nice room with large balcony and lovely neighborhood view, however there is very little closet space and no dressers.

The pop-up drain in the shower, which I reported on each of our first 2 days. There was no communication on the status of the repair until I was checking out and I was told the part had to be ordered. The only other complaint would be that they use very cheap towels.

Spa was well maintained and had much better-quality towels

Walking in neighborhood felt very safe day or night.

Great hotel, very well located, room was very comfortable with an attention to details (expresso machine, bathrobe and slippers for the spa, yoga mat). I was upgraded to a top floor room with a small balcony, very pleasant. Breakfast was good, I used the gym and, although it was small I found quality cardiovascular equipment in a very clean room. Will definitely go back on my own or with my partner.

This boutique hotel does a lot with the space it has to make it a welcoming and homely atmosphere.

The wellness centre is incredible for a hotel of this size.

The bedroom was great and the staff were attentive.

The breakfast was excellent.

Will definitely stay here again

We came as a couple and enjoyed the spa facilities (booking required for a 1 hour slot). The staff was very attentive and available. The room was large, comfortable and quiet, which we appreciated. The neighborhood is quiet, there is a supermarket and several restaurants nearby - convenient in these times of Covid.

Great hotel, best amenities and great staff always there to help you. Nice and clean My boys and i enjoyed our trip.The hotel was very close to the metro and essential shops. Thank you would definitely come back

I booked this holiday for my in-laws as a birthday/anniversary present. As I wasn't going with them I had a lot of contact with the hotel staff in advance to make arrangements for my mother-in-law who is disabled. They could not do enough to help things run smoothly, even offering to keep her wheelchair at reception to give them more space in the room (she does not need it all the time), and giving advice about nearby parking facilities. Sadly when the Coronavirus hit I had to cancel the trip, but still the staff were very helpful and understanding and made the whole process hassle-free. I would happily stay with them in the future based on this excellent service.

Clean, nice hotel with a great neighborhood. We were about an hour walk to most of the big attractions (Eiffel Tower, Norte Dame, The Lourve). Some days we walked and some days we ubered or took the metro. Both Uber and Metro are easily navigated here. There is a metro very close by that runs conveniently through the city. Transferring was easy and the ride to Versaille was also a breeze.

The neighborhood that the hotel is in has cute coffee shops, great restaurants, and small markets for essentials. We loved the coffee shop/bar at the end of the block. They small authentic breakfast was everything we needed after a long night of flying.

The hotel staff is friendly and speaks English well. The only slight issue we experienced was the first room they put us in had a very strange smell. It smelled like food had been left to rot somewhere in the room. The man who check us in promptly came up and brought 2 new keys with him. He switched out room and even upgraded us. I would say if you have traveling with a decent amount of luggage and plan to be there for longer than a couple nights, the larger room was ideal, so maybe splurge a little for the extra space. If we had not lucked out we would have been in pretty tight quarters. We didn’t spend a LOT of time in the room but after exploring a ton over a few day period, a day of rest was nice.

Our room consisted of a queen bed and a side couch/bed that you could easily sleep on if needed. We used it for extra space to spread out clothing and luggage. The closet is spacious, but be careful when opening. The unique design will either break your shin or take your head off if you open it too quickly. The mini bar appears to be complimentary daily, but it is not. We only drank the water and 2 beers, but realized we were being charged daily. Go to the local grocer for water. The large bottles there were a fraction of what they charge for the tiny Evian.

The hotel offers breakfast for a fee and we were happy we paid for it. Finding breakfast is hard as hours of operation in Paris are not like US. Also, other than coffee and baguette, you won’t find much else elsewhere. We did enjoy the French staples of croissant, baguette and other breads but the other items (eggs, yogurt, cheese/meats, and fruit) were great to have to keep up sustained almost until dinner.

The spa and pool area are wonderful. We loved the pool and steam room and spent an hour there daily after a long day of exploring. We did not use the work out room but I did witness one man cleaning the room throughly from top to bottom, which was nice to see. They provide robes and towels for you in the locker rooms.

Sidenote: We did a “Welcome to Paris” tour for about 2 hours when we first arrived. We met with a local guide who sat with us in a coffee shop and gave us a run down on things we would need to know while we were there. Honestly, I highly recommend this. She explained a lot to us in that time and even took us to the metro to show us how to purchase tickets and navigate it. We are from Chicago, so railway systems are not new to us. However, being in another country it was nice to have a little bit of knowledge on operations at the beginning of our trip. She also walked us to come shops within a 2 block radius of the hotel and showed us some great nearby restaurants.

Rooms were nice, although with compromises sadly.

We had to move rooms, first room was really, really small at front of hotel which was noisy at night from bars! But had a really nice shower.

Second room was at the rear, which was quieter, with a bath and larger, but this time sadly the shower was not the best as it frequently changed temperature and didn't fit quite right for directioning which was frustrating!

Both had no mirror in the room?? We asked at reception but they had nothing available for any room even though this was a known issue? This is a small addition that can make getting ready so much easier and comfortable, so a shame it's not been addressed.

Spa was very, very nice, especially if you catch the timing right. Its clean and everything worked well and as we had hoped, all except the jacuzzi function. The steam room was really nice, aromatherapy scent was lovely, followed by a tropical shower = very nice.

Staff were really helpful and kind, they helped make our stay more comfortable and pleasant.

Location was good, close to 2 metros which can get you literally everywhere, walkable to a large number of sights and also well equipped with food, bars and mini markets. Was well located for our trip and needs.

Hotel is in a perfect location shops bars cafes all around 3 minute walk to metro and if you prefer to walk only 20 minutes to eiffel tower or 35 mins to the louvre. Hotel was spotlessly clean and the staff really friendly and helpful. Will definitely be returning.

The hotel is stylish and clean, during our 3 nights stay our room was attended too each day (i.e. bed made, towels folded etc) which was great to come back to after a day exploring the city.

The reception was able to provide restaurant recommendations which were very local and did not disappoint.

I would recommend checking all charges, deposits etc when booking and ensure you take the payment method you used for the booking with you for check in as we had some issues. However, the hotel contacted us after the visit and provide explanations into these.

We stayed for 3 days and had a very good experience. Our room 601 faced the courtyard so it was really quiet at night!! The room was pretty good in regards to Size, the bathroom was good with hot rag angerufen for towels, bathrobes, quote a lot of space for the stuff. The Hotel has a nice lounge area were you can sit and relax with an honesty bar. Breakfast was 15 € per Person, fair Price for a City Hotel. There was a good selection of cheese, egg with bacon, Salmon, good Croissants and different bread and Müsli. The room itself isnt super stylish but it does its purpose. The Hotel is just 5 minutes from the Metro which makes it also ideal. Would go there again.

Very luxurious hotel. The staff was very nice and accommodating. I loved the breakfast buffet and the SPA with a big pool, sauna and hammam. I loved to hang around with a bathrobe and slippers. We stayed in the beautiful 701 room with terrasse and living room.
I want to go back !

We spend one night in this hotel in February and could not have been happier about the service, the room and the location.
Ideally located, we did many walks in the neighborhood, it is also very well connected close to the metro station.
The hotel itself was modern, and design.
We enjoyed the honesty bar very much, were we had a after diner drinks in the comfortable sofas enjoying e few gin and tonics next to an artificial fire place.
The staff was very accommodating and going above and beyond to make sure we were having an excellent stay.

Stayed here in Feb - great location for metro and transport for all the sites. Beautiful neighbourhood, with mix of local shops, pubs etc.
Facilities in the hotel were superb with good pool and spa
Staff very helpful with quality suggestions for where to eat in the evening and good variety of options.
We will love to return for another trip.

We stayed here for 4 night the staff were very professional the hotel was very clean with a great breakfast with lots of choices would highly recommend this hotel to anyone I will definitely be returning

We had a very nice stay, the hotel is nicely situated in walking distance to the Eiffel tower and the exhibition halls of Porte de Versailles. The breakfast buffet has a large choice of fruits, bread etc.
Can only recommend!

Really helpful pre-stay questionnaire seeking our requirements and great reviews before we arrived. In addition, after asking a local person for directions, we were told it is a nice hotel, so great start.

Reception very helpful and excellent English spoken, good for a novice with French! Only stayed for one night (visiting a local exhibition) but came any feeling happy, excellent spa facilities and nice breakfast (the hot food could have been hotter) and really helpful staff on hand.

Rooms, very clean and tidy, nice bathroom but would have liked the beds to be separated (as requested on the questionnaire) but easy job for us.

I would definitely come back if/when travelling to Paris again.

Personaly for me the best hotel in town. Like the big pool and Sauna so much. Rooms and beeds are comfortable. Breakfeast is delicious. A wounderful hotel for a business trip.
Please note its not a family hotel (kids).

Recently stayed and what I thought would a pleasant stay was disappointing.
I won’t discuss room size as it’s Paris and you don’t expect big rooms. However a suite which lacked cupboard space, poor shower and lack of lighting.
Staff well they really help the French reputation. Don’t acknowledge you or talk to you. Staff taking guest lifts always seems wrong to me.
Ironing board left in a corridor for 2 days.
Breakfast don’t book it or take it. We were told it was available until 11am in the breakfast room and 10.30 in your room. No Information in the room on how to order so we called down and were told you can have bread and a hot drink best you have it in the breakfast room to get more choice. Message received, they don’t want to do room service
We went to the breakfast room the waitress was clearing the tables at 9.30, 2 hours before the end of breakfast. No plates on 2/3 of the tables so we had to steel one from neighbouring table. And the choice and quality was just poor. You get better breakfast in an Ibis.
As in the title you can find better

We booked the Eiffel Blomet, based on the reviews we read and the location that was near most everything we wanted to see while in Paris. I work in the travel industry, and have spent 20 years of my career working for major brand hotels. In my current business, I travel a lot, and log many nights in hotels each year. Yes, I'm a bit picky.

The hotel is located in a charming neighborhood, near restaurants, cafe's, and bars. We loved the feeling of being part of the neighborhood, and enjoying the local vibe.

The hotel is the perfect example of a "Boutique" property. The staff is so polite and welcoming. The room was small, but perfectly appointed, clean and very comfortable. The restaurant breakfast is a good way to start the day. They could work on adding a few more food options, but overall it was good and made it easy for us to get our day off to a good start!

We walked to everything we wanted to see. The Eiffel Tower is maybe a 20-30 minute walk, the Pantheon about the same. It's a short walk to the Javel train station for a quick trip to Versailles. If you're wanting to feel like Parisian, stay at the Eiffel Blomet.

The hotel is located in a quiet street however really close to a few underground stations and other busier streets, only about 20 minutes on foot from the Tour Eiffel. Really helpful and professional but also very friendly staff, both in the breakfast room and at the hotel reception. Our room was nice, and incredibly quiet, even with an opened window - we really appreciated that. The hotel is very clean, cosy, and it has a small interior pool. Breakfast? Excellent. Sufficient variety of fresh and tasty French food. Would love to go there again anytime.

Lovely hotel, comfortable rooms with friendly helpful staff and excellent facilities. We previously stayed next to the Eiffel Tower but much preferred this location. It was a very easy 25 walk to the Eiffel Tower and you have such a selection of bars and cafes, fruit shops, hairdressers, supermarket in fact a very local experience. We thoroughly enjoyed the heated pool and two saunas.

My wife Valerie and I visited Hotel Eiffel Blomet for two nights in early October 2019.We were immediately impressed by the welcome afforded us by the reception staff, and the comfort of the ground floor lounge. The latter was matched by the cleanliness and obvious effort that had been imposed on our bedroom by the staff, Our en suite facilities also were perfect! Our two days' visit to Paris was enhanced by an excellent buffet style breakfast in the well appointed ground floor restaurant, as well as by the attentive and helpful staff. Again the reception staff were most helpful in providing directions to the many famous tourist attractions situated within walking distance - a vital requirement as over forty years had passed since our last visit to Paris!
Our final departure from the Hotel for the Gare du Nord was aided by a call for a prompt taxi by the Concierge!
I have no adverse criticisms whatsoever to make relating to the Hotel Eiffel Blomet. We are looking forward to returning to spend more time in this beautiful City.

My Wife & I were overjoyed to have stayed at Hotel Eiffel Blomet; it is a quality hotel in aesthetic terms and in its staff and services. We arrived in the middle of a long strike action and received some keen intel from the staff re best options for travel and state of emotion in the city; this was appreciated. Staff were always on hand and happy to assist. Room was great and had a nice street view with an added bonus of receiving the morning sun when it finally came out! The pool and spa helped make our stay given the miles of walking this was both a good prep and wind down opportunity.
Breakfast in bed for 1 morning of our stay was money well spent - delicious:)
Location of Hotel is perfect as not too far from main tourist attractions and also smack bang in the middle of its own community - just around corner are great local shops, bars and eateries.
The people of Paris for being so long into a strike were in the main surprisingly up beat which was very surprising and of course good news for us as when we asked for directions or attended local trade we were always made welcome or assisted.
we will definitely return to this great city
David & Kerry

Lovely hotel, staff were helpful and friendly... rooms were nice and clean... lots of shops nearby... Eiffel tower is about 25 minute walk from the hotel, but you can hire scooters which make it an easy travel...Macdonalds is round the corner which was the best as i had a 12 year old with me who wasnt too keen on trying different types of foods lol... theres couple of convenience stores round the corner too so u can buy snacks.. loved using the sauna, steam room and pool area.. only downfall was that there was lots of hair by the pool area and in the steam room for a number of days making me believe it wasnt cleaned regularly... overall a great stay...

Loved our stay there. The location was very convenient with good restaurants nearby and a short walk to the metro. Room was decent size for Paris but the shower was amazing. We loved and used the swimming pool and really enjoyed the breakfast on site. Will love to stay here again.

This was a beautiful hotel and excellent location

Proximal to the largest landmarks with a 25 minute walk or 15 minute taxi ride. We procured a room on the top floor which had a pleasant view and loved how clean the area was.

Having added the romance package, was very content with the layout and care the staff took to set up the room.

Staff were friendly and incredibly helpful with maps and recommendations on best places to eat and visit

The short vacation here was truly made that bit more special by the accommodation and will definitely recall this hotel for future visits to the Paris area

Enter Hotel Eiffel Blomet and just enjoy everything about this establishment. It’s in a terrific position close to the Hotel de Ville for this Arrondisement and has two little parks very close to the front door. Every member of staff looks after your every need and all this is provided at an excellent price. Room compact but well supplied with everything for a superb stay.

Wonderfull hotel, centrally located in Paris. Comfortabel rooms, on the small side, but excellent decorated. Nice “open bar” and breakfast area. Staff sometimes a bit “short and task oriented”. Overall great place to stay and ps: the pool is super!!!!

Great hotel, nice room clean, wide ,comfortable bed and services, good amenities , nice decoration, and a varied and excellent breakfast. I will repeat in other travel to Paris, great staff serving us!

Superb hotel, located quite close to Eiffel Tower.
Spotless room and bathroom, super comfy bed and high quality bed sheets. Delicious breakfast with lots of choices, e.g. yogurt, cereal, fruit, pancakes, eggs, croissants, pastries, coffee, tea, juice, etc.
Great spa amenities!

This hotel works for me partly because it is in the neighborhood where my friend lives. But forget that, it's an excellent location for anybody. Near the 12 Metro and lots of buses you are are also practically next door to a patisserie with one of the best baguettes in Paris (as well as delicious everything else), close to more than one cheese shop, foie gras store, lots of cafes, and walking distance to excellent restaurants. You're a couple of blocks up Blomet from one of the best night-time looks at the sparkling Tour Eiffel. There's a twice-a-week morning food market close by on Convention and you can walk over to Commerce for shopping and more cafes. The park Lambert is a treat in all seasons. Vaugirard offers shopping too and the Monoprix on Vaugirard is a really good one. As for the hotel, it's excellent. Staff is pleasant, lobby is comfortable. Our room was tiny but well done - in truth, really a room for one because storage space is minimal (really minimal). There are ways they could improve the storage and hopefully they will. Bathroom is very good. The bed and pillows were great (and it's rare, in my experience, to get good pillows). We tried breakfast once and it was only okay. We did use both the pool and the exercise room - they are really a bonus to have at a small hotel.

We stayed at the Hotel Eiffel Blomet while visiting our daughter who is studying in Paris. It is the perfect location in the 15th. Close to cafes and the Eiffel Tower and Les Invalides. The hotel is on a side street off a small square. Despite being in a room on the street side next to the elevator the noise level was very low. The rooms are a nice size with a lovely bed, sofa and small table and chairs. The bathrooms are smaller but you have everything you need. I love the warm towel racks! The only reason it's not getting 5 stars is that there is no bar. There is an honesty bar with varied offerings but no proper bar set up. Other than that the perfect little hotel! We enjoyed our stay very much.

Very nice and elegant hotel. Location is great, good restaurants and shops(cheese, meat, wine) nearby.
I loved the breakfast with great Kusmitea selection, and fresh pastries. It worth the price definetly.
You can find nespresso coffeemashine in the room, which is a good start of the day.
We would definetly stay here next time.

Extremely stylish and clean hotel.
All staff were helpful, attentive and knowledgeable.
Breakfast is delicious and there is a very good selection of foods.
The Spa facilities are modern, luxurious and just what you need before or after a fun day in Paris!

Stayed at the Hotel EIffel Blomet on my first trip to Paris and turned out to be an awesome hotel with great personel, very nice rooms and offered an excellent breakfast. I would recommend staying at this hotel and I would definitely book it again,

We stayed for 2 nights in October to attend an event nearby over a weekend.

The hotel has clearly been recently refurbished and the public areas of the hotel look smart and like they have had some care put into them. Whilst small, the lobby area and breakfast buffet have everything they need for a comfortable stay. The rooms also seem very small (I guess that's typical for an old city centre hotel) and most of them overlook a rather dingey courtyard area, so end up feeling rather dark and uninviting. The bed was comfortable and there was plentiful hot water for a good shower, so at least the essentials were covered.

Service-wise, our rooms weren't ready until almost 6pm on the day of our arrival, which is pretty poor going. We also found that the staff who were supposed to be attending to the breakfast area were mostly hiding in the kitchen chatting each morning.

As for the location, you're about 5 minutes walk to the nearest metro station, which is then about 15-20 minutes to the city centre and the various tourist attractions. Around the hotel are a variety of cafes and restaurants, some good, some bad, but all rather pricey, but I think that's just symptomatic of Paris rather than the area of the hotel.

Overall, a pleasant stay, but there are better hotels in the city.

Nice hotel. Would certainly come back. Room, staff, food (breakfast) and location were all good. 방도 좋고, 직원들도 친절해요...위치도 괜찮구요. 아침 식사는 보통 정도 되구요...출장 땜에 왔는데, 개인적으로 여행와도 다시 올 것 같아요. 며칠 전에 강 위쪽에서 이틀 지냈는데, 그 호텔에 비하면 가격 차이는 크지 않은데, 방은 좀 더 여유로운 것 같아요...

We stayed one night at the Hotel. Staff was very friendly. didn't catch the name of one of the Staff. I did hear her say she was from San Diego, California. She was very helpful to us. Being Americans in Paris and not speaking French it's nice to have an English speaking person to help out. Room was small but, for Paris it was accommodating.
